(97,	1,	'2018-11-02 03:04:29',	'2018-11-02 03:04:29',	'Leitis in Waiting is the story of Joey Mataele and the Tonga Leitis, an intrepid group of Indigenous transgender women fighting a rising tide of religious fundamentalism in their South Pacific Kingdom. With unexpected humour and extraordinary access to the royal family, the film follows Joey as she organises an exuberant beauty pageant, presided over by a princess, shelters a young contestant rejected by her family, and spars with evangelicals threatening to resurrect British colonial laws that would criminalise the Leitis’ lives. This is an inside story, created by a transgender Polynesian woman who once competed in Joey’s beauty pageant.',	'LEITIS IN WAITING',	'',	'publish',	'closed',	'closed',	'',	'a-woman-captured-sydney-copy-copy-copy-copy-copy-copy-copy-copy-copy',	'',	'',	'2018-11-02 04:06:47',	'2018-11-02 04:06:47',	'',	0,	'http://localhost:3157/ruby/?event=a-woman-captured-sydney-copy-copy-copy-copy-copy-copy-copy-copy-copy',	0,	'event',	'',	0),
